r, frame work agreement, subscription agreement, government approvals, restructuring and integration. Lead external consulting and investment banks. Fully covered the whole global M&A process, enhanced my M&A leadership skills, global acquisition capability, due diligence & negotiation expertise, financial and legal knowledge. \\n2. Bio-energy (new energy) Project. Signed Framework agreement with a leading Chinese bio-energy company for biomass based fuel, bio-butanol and other bio-products. \\n3. Rosneft Project. Signed agreement for Polyethylene, polypropylene, and other polymer distribution in Asia Pacific Region. Studied the investment opportunity in Rosneft (the biggest Russian oil company) far eastern refineries. \\n4. Keep good network and hold regular meetings with investment banks including Merrill Lynch, UBS, RBS etc (with Global head, Managing Directors) and key industry executive directors such as DuPont, Bayer, DSM, Total, BP, GSK, ChemChina, P&G. etc. Maintain good relationship with government authorities such as NDRC, MOFCOM and Investors (both Industrial companies and PE).\\n\\nExpertise: General Management, Investment, M&A, Strategy, Business Development\",\"title\":\"Business Development and Strategy Director\",\"region\":\"urn:li:fs_region:(cn,8911)\",\"rangeDate\":\"2009-12至2011-12\"},{\"companyName\":\"Procter & Gamble\",\"description\":\"Global Business Development (GBD), P&G (Procter & Gamble), a Fortune 500 Multinational Corporation. UK, USA and China experience \\n\\nJoined the Company in UK. Work for corporate consulting, business development, M&A, and open innovation. Leading P&G “Global Business Development” (GBD) and “open innovation”. Developed the business through M&A and Cooperation. Developed the Disruptive Market Innovation (DMI) model to orient work. \\n\\nSelected Projects (non-confidential) : \\n1. Softto Project. Due diligence for a functional cosmetic company Softto Co., Ltd. \\n2. P&G innovation & sustainable projects. Applied