ogies and integration best practices.\\n\\nCoordinate assigned deliverable schedules to ensure client’s timelines are met and provide guidance to clients or service partners on integration strategies.\\n\\nResponsible for translating client’s business requirements into specific systems, applications or process designs for very large complex IT solutions and integrating architecture.\\n\\nAct as an advocate for the client as the ultimate authority on the architecture designed to address client business problems and provide direction for design activities. Often project-based and working remotely or at customer sites.\\n\\nDesign, build, test, and deploy integration systems with in depth expertise in the Workday solution. Skills to perform such tasks include knowledge in technical tools and programming languages (JavaScript, XSLT, XML, XPath, etc.), and ability to analyze business requirements.\",\"title\":\"Principal Integration Consultant\",\"rangeDate\":\"2016-10\"},{\"locationName\":\"U.S. / Virtual\",\"companyName\":\"NorthgateArinso (formerly Arinso)\",\"description\":\"Executed and managed installation and implementation of technology solutions for SAP Business suite for the HCM specific industry (NetWeaver 2004 and higher with single and dual-stack ABAP+Java, EP, for Oracle on Linux and Windows). Integration of architectural components, such as SSO solutions with Kerberos, SAML v1.x and SAML v2.x.\",\"title\":\"Senior SAP Technology Consultant\",\"rangeDate\":\"2008-10至2011-5\"},{\"locationName\":\"Greater Atlanta Area\",\"companyName\":\"Workday\",\"description\":\"See Description for Principal Integration Consultant at Workday.\",\"title\":\"Senior Integration Consultant\",\"rangeDate\":\"2013-3至2016-10\"}]', '[\"Oracle\",\"SAP HR\",\"Integration\",\"SAP\"]', 'zhangcheung', '2017-05-17 16:06:32');
